# Next.js 15 App Router Conventions

## File Conventions

- `app/layout.tsx` — root layout, wraps all pages, must include `<html>` and `<body>`
- `app/page.tsx` — route segment UI, Server Component by default
- `app/loading.tsx` — Suspense boundary for the segment
- `app/error.tsx` — error boundary (`'use client'` required)
- `app/not-found.tsx` — 404 UI
- `app/[slug]/page.tsx` — dynamic segment

## Server vs Client Components

Default is **Server Component**. Add `'use client'` only when needed:

```tsx
// ✅ Server Component — data fetching, no hooks/events
export default async function Page() {
  const data = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data').then(r => r.json())
  return <main>{data.title}</main>
}

// ✅ Client Component — interactivity, hooks, browser APIs
'use client'
import { useState } from 'react'
export function Counter() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0)
  return <button onClick={() => setCount(c => c + 1)}>{count}</button>
}
```

## Data Fetching

```tsx
// ✅ Fetch with caching control
const data = await fetch('https://api.example.com', {
  cache: 'force-cache',        // SSG-like
  next: { revalidate: 60 },   // ISR — revalidate every 60s
})

// ✅ Dynamic (no cache)
const data = await fetch('https://api.example.com', { cache: 'no-store' })
```

## Metadata

```tsx
// Static
export const metadata = { title: 'Page Title', description: '...' }

// Dynamic
export async function generateMetadata({ params }) {
  return { title: `Post: ${params.slug}` }
}
```

## Route Handlers (API)

```ts
// app/api/items/route.ts
import { NextResponse } from 'next/server'

export async function GET() {
  return NextResponse.json({ items: [] })
}

export async function POST(request: Request) {
  const body = await request.json()
  return NextResponse.json({ created: body }, { status: 201 })
}
```

## Rules

- Prefer Server Components; push `'use client'` to the leaves
- Use `next/image` for all `<img>` — never raw `<img>` tags
- Use `next/link` for internal navigation — never `<a href>`
- Co-locate component files next to the route segment that uses them
- Type `params` and `searchParams` as `Promise<{...}>` (Next.js 15+)
